To improve supervision of teachers, the Teachers Service Commission has bought motorbikes for subcounty TSC officers in Trans Nzoia.TSC county director Ibrahim Adan flagged off three motorbikes for Kwanza, Trans Nzoia West and Trans Nzoia East subcounties. He said they will increase the mobility of subcounty officers to monitor the progress of teacher programmes.He said the officers will conduct routine visits to implement the agenda of the commission and the Ministry of Education. &ldquo;We want to increase our visibility in our schools to ensure teachers are adhering to better teaching practices,&rdquo; he said.Adan said it will help fast-track reforms of TSC, such as performance contracts, teachers&rsquo; performance appraisal and programmes like Tusome and Pride, among others. Head teachers now will not have to visit headquarters.